 The Mpumalanga Tourism and Parks Agency (MTPA) has advised that all view sites and attractions in Blyde River Canyon Nature Reserve will be closed from this morning (July 28) until further notice. This includes Bourke’s Luck Potholes, the Three Rondavels, God’s Window,the  Pinnacle and Swadini. Day hiking trails, however, remain open. The MTPA apologises for the inconvenience while it prepares the sites to be fully compliant with Covid-19 protocols. ALSO READ: At least 12 Covid-19 cases recorded at Mpumalanga police stations in one week MTPA spokesperson, Kholofelo Nkambule said, “There is a delay in the delivery of additional PPE as well as cleaning material. Therefore, for the safety of our staff and visitors the sites will be closed temporarily.”